:[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":true,"disclosed_at":"2018-12-22T16:16:11.543Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2018-12-22T16:16:11.427Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2018-12-22T11:34:29.886Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"An attacker can persistently block access to any/all redirects on www.hackerone.com by using cache poisoning with the X-Forwarded-Port or X-Forwarded-Host headers to redirect users to an invalid port.\n\nTo replicate: \n```curl -H 'X-Forwarded-Port: 123' https://www.hackerone.com/index.php?dontpoisoneveryone=1```\nThen try to load https://www.hackerone.com/index.php?dontpoisoneveryone=1 in your browser.\n\nThis attack can also be done using the X-Forwarded-Host header:\n```curl -H 'X-Forwarded-Host: www.hackerone.com:123' https://www.hackerone.com/index.php?dontpoisoneveryone=1```\n\n\nFor more information on the theory behind this attack, check out https://portswigger.net/blog/practical-web-cache-poisoning\n\n## Impact\n\nAn attacker can persistently block access to any/all redirects on www.hackerone.com","bounty_amount":"2500.0","formatted_bounty":"$2,500","weakness":{"id":48,"name":"Uncontrolled Resource Consumption"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":345778,"file_name":"Screen_Shot_2018-09-13_at_11.08.12.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/345/778/6fece49a309a48d571c81a46aa7469626f5130ac/Screen_Shot_2018-09-13_at_11.08.12.png?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22Screen_Shot_2018-09-13_at_11.08.12.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27Screen_Shot_2018-09-13_at_11.08.12.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQXIKJZ7C2%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T093945Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX